snippet.textDisplay:
We had our baby girl a year ago. We put her on probiotics right when we got home from the hospital and she was never colicky, gassy and never went through the purple crying stage.

The strain of bacteria you specifically should look out for is B. Infantis. Do your research on it. It is often overlooked by medical professionals.

The brand we bought was by corganics- their gutpro infant formula. It is free of all known allergens that can sometimes affect baby.

Sending you love through this challenging time! Having a brand new baby can be challenging and scary but it's the most amazing thing!

Omg that literally happens to almost all babies up to about 3 months. So change your attitude with the what the doctor told you.
Yes she’s going to cry and scream for weeks because she has gas. You just need to watch what you eat and rub her tummy and flex her legs up towards her belly to help her relive the gas.
The person with the ear infection got there before you and was probably waiting longer than you guys. Emergency rooms take whoever is worse and baby gas isn’t deadly.

snippet.textDisplay: As an ER nurse I can tell you any time you call a hospital they are going to tell you to come in as it’s a liability to tell you not to. Also please please please for anyone who thinks there is something wrong with their infant bring them to a children’s hospital!! There is absolutely nothing a normal ER can do for an infant besides stabilize them and transfer them to a children’s hospital. With the symptoms she had and her normal vitals any ER you went to would have told you the same thing and told you to follow up with your pediatrician. I’m sorry you had to wait so long to be sent home but just in the future if there is something seriously wrong with her bring her to a children’s hospital because normal ER don’t have pediatricians :(

snippet.textDisplay: When my baby was born he was like that every day he only slept for like 20 or 25 minutes and then wake up to cry again. It was due to the baby formula he used to spit up every single time he had milk like a lot up to the point that we had to take him to a specialist and changed his formula like at least 5 times it was very very stressful and I couldn't breast feed due to some health issues I felt so bad seeing him in such pain I completely understand you guys. There are some drops that you can give her if it is colic it helped my baby a lot! He is almost 10 months old and he is healthy no more spit ups and he sleeps a lot more than those 25 minutes 😂🙌🏽. Hope everything goes well with baby soul 💗 love you guys. You are such great parents she is so blessed to have you guys as parents.

snippet.textDisplay: My son was super Colicky. He would hit the "Witching Hour" around 4 and would cry and be so uncomfortable till about 9pm. What really helped me was one: My Pediatrician had twilight hours until 10pm that could really help you if something happens later in the evening, two: I found a great infant probiotic. Once I put him on the probiotics he was a whole new baby. Hope this helps!

snippet.textDisplay: Whenever that happens to your baby. She is colic, I also had a c section and my baby at exactly 2 weeks old cried just as you described. Doctors will tell she is too young to be diagnosed with colic but i don’t believe that’s true. Look up all the signs for baby with colic. Oh and my baby suffered from it until she was 5 months it was really bad, I wish someone would’ve told me right away I would’ve been way more prepared. All things said I really really wish this is not the case with your baby and hopefully it was just that day.  God bless her💕
